The Shareholders’ Funds of Wapic Insurance Plc rose to N24 billion in June 2020, up from N19 billion it was in December, 2019. This translates to N5 billion increase within the first half of the year. Meanwhile, from June 2019 to June 2020, the Wapic Insurance group grew its premium position by 8 per cent year-on-year(YoY) basis to close at N9.34billion in June, 2020, up from N8.6 billion in June, 2019. Its underwriting profit position equally grew by 58 per cent to N2 billion compared with the N1.3 billion recorded in June, 2019. This, the company said, was driven by the growth in its premium position and fees and commission income. While its claims expenses slightly dropped from N2.7 billion it recorded in June, 2019 to N2.6 billion in June 2020, its investment income rose to N500 million from N430 million within the period under review. Moreover, net income grew to N2.9 billion from N1.8 billion in June 2019, even as its profit after tax jumped to N654 million from N305 million within the period under review. Speaking on this development, managing director, Wapic Insurance Plc, Mrs. Yinka Adekoya, said, despite the prevailing conditions in the economy that may have impacted sign on of new business, renewal rate, installment payment of premium, her insurer delivered a commendable performance in the first half of 2020. According to her, “We remain relentless in our Gross Written Premium(GWP) growth drive this year in line with our revised growth expectations following the impact of the global pandemic on insurance operations. With the success of our digital transformation, we would constructively harness the opportunities that abound during this period with the aid of technology.”